<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5693] BUILTIN should say passwords are hashed not encrypted</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5693</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Many places in the BUILTIN authentication code it is said that passwords are encrypted before they are stored in the database. It would be more accurate to say that the passwords are hashed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
